OPEN HOUSE POSTPONED: Due to a forecast for severe weather on Saturday, April 22, our Open House Celebration has been rescheduled until Saturday, May 6. We apologize for any inconvenience that this may cause, but much of the event was to have been outside and our Old Friends will be upset about the weather. \nhttps://www.facebook.com/events/1856866234583421/

Middle TN Folks!! Our Open House is next Saturday.

This is our Official Grand Opening! We will have Food, Information about Old Friends Senior Dog Sanctuary and flash tours (approximately 10 minute tours every twenty minutes for up to 6 people per tour) through the sanctuary. Our Gift Shop, Ye Olde Friends Shoppe, will be open during this time. We hope to see you there!

No children under 13 years old will be allowed on the tours. We will, however, have other kid friendly activities.

No personal dogs will allowed inside GrandPaw's Gardens. It will be too upsetting for our Old Friends.

FAQs

What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?

Waldmann encourages attendees to bike/walk and is located near Metro Transit bus lines 54 & 74. Onstreet parking is avaiable on West 7th, (Note: many residential street have permit parking regulations).

What can I bring into the event?

Bring yourself and interested friends. Be prepared to help support the Kickstarter campaign during the event. 

How can I contact the organizer with any questions?

Contact Adam Yust with any questions at waldmannbrewery@gmail.com.

Join us for this unique conversation with the craftsman and carpenters that are helping to bring Waldmann back to life. This is an insider's guide to learn more about Waldmann, and the detailed work being done behind the scenes. Carpenters will discuss the processes, tools, and practices of the 1850s that are once again being used to restore Waldmann - 160 years later. If you like plain talk and can hammer a point home, join us and tell your friends!

Hello,

We are so close, at 70% as of today...but with only 4 days to go, feel so far from the goal.  It ends on Tuesday, at 11:59 PM.  If we don't make our goal we get nothing.

So I am reaching out to ask everyone to dig just a little deeper.  There are over 300 backers on the SENIORS campaign.  If each of you could give $10 more towards your pledge, we would be that much closer.  But everything helps, $1 helps, $5 helps, anything and everything.  Please dig deep and help us share these amazing stories.

And please continue sharing.  We will do it...together!

Thank you,
Gorman Bechard

We here at Card Castle would like to take a moment and say Happy Mothers day!

Check out Card Castle: a new slap card game with a medieval fantasy theme. Think Game of Thrones meets Slap Jack!
Even a tiny pledge of $1 helps us to increase our daily backer count and boost our rankings on the Kickstarter site! This makes Card Castle more visible to other potential backers, plus you'll be automatically looped into all Card Castle progress. :)
If the game looks fun for you or someone you know, pledging at a higher reward level will get you a copy (or copies) of the game once the project funds and production is completed! If we don't reach our fundraising goal, all money pledged will be automatically refunded with no action needed on your part.
Feel free to share with anyone you think might be interested in Card Castle!
Thanks again for being awesome fans!
